<paragraph id="1F12A470516CC75478A6F9E2FC3CF8BD" blockId="1.[151,1436,1661,1868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="2DD97862516CC75478A6F9E2FBEFF966" bold="true" box="[151,1079,1661,1688]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">
Diagnosis for genus (modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="7B3CD981516CC7547A70F9E2FC8AF969" author="Corona, E. M. &amp; Brown, B. V." box="[577,850,1661,1688]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" pagination="21 - 38" refId="ref17875" refString="Corona, E. M. &amp; Brown, B. V. (2005) The Central American species of Diplonevra Lioy (Diptera: Phoridae). Zootaxa, 1050 (1), 21 - 38. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1050.1.3" type="journal article" year="2005">Corona &amp; Brown 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7B3CD981516CC7547B6FF9E2FBF2F966" author="Liu, G. C. &amp; Yang, M." box="[862,1066,1661,1688]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" pagination="31 - 51" refId="ref18651" refString="Liu, G. C. &amp; Yang, M. (2016) A taxonomic revision of the genus Diplonevra Lioy (Diptera: Phoridae) from China. Zootaxa, 4205 (1), 31 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4205.1.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Liu &amp; Yang 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Frons with one pair of reclinate supra-antennal bristles. Anepisternum bare, undivided. Midtibia with one pair of bristles on basal half (one anterodorsal, one posterodorsal). Inner face of male trochanter and basal portion of hind femur usually with modified stout setae and hairs. Hind tibia with 2 or 3 dorsal longitudinal setal palisades. Wing vein R 
<subScript id="8329A635516CC7547CAFF963FB60F8FB" attach="left" box="[1182,1208,1788,1802]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">2+3</subScript>
present. One to few setae limited to basal quarter of vein Rs. More than single alular seta present. Male cercus (=anal tube of 
<bibRefCitation id="7B3CD981516CC7547D7CF891FF08F8BD" author="Disney, R. H. L." pageId="1" pageNumber="239" pagination="33 - 39" refId="ref18001" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1990) A key to Diplonevra males of the Australasian and Oriental Regions, including two new species (Diptera, Phoridae). Entomologica Fennica, 1, 33 - 39. https: // doi. org / 10.33338 / ef. 83355" type="journal article" year="1990">Disney 1990</bibRefCitation>
) cylindrically elongated with one pair of small sclerites dorsoapically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
